title: SpaceX breaks pad turnaround record in support of Starlink
summary: The first of two Starlink launches in close succession, Starlink Group 5-4 lifted off at 12:10 AM EST (05:10 UTC) on Sunday, Feb. 12. The mission broke the pad turnaround record for both Space Launch Complex 40 (SLC-40) at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station in Florida and the overall record across all three Falcon 9 launch pads.

title: Russian cargo ship docks as second Progress suffers sudden loss of coolant
summary: A Russian Progress supply ship successfully docked with the International Space Station early Saturday but in an unlikely, presumed coincidence, another Progress, docked at a different port, suffered a sudden loss of coolant similar to an incident that disabled a Soyuz crew ship in December.
